# Project Rules for Collaborative Editor Sample

## Code Standards
- All code comments must be in English
- All documentation must be in English
- Use clear, descriptive variable and function names
- Follow JavaScript/React best practices

## Commit Guidelines
- **DO NOT commit** any files containing:
  - License violations or proprietary code
  - Sensitive security information (API keys, passwords, tokens, secrets)
  - Personal credentials or authentication data
  - Private keys or certificates
  - Environment files with actual secrets (.env files with real values)
  
- **DO commit**:
  - Source code with MIT or open-source licensed dependencies only
  - Documentation files
  - Configuration files (without sensitive data)
  - Example .env files with placeholder values only

## Security Best Practices
- Never hardcode secrets in source code
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Keep dependencies updated and audit regularly
- Review third-party packages for security vulnerabilities

## Dependencies
- Only use MIT licensed or compatible open-source packages
- Ensure all dependencies are free to use commercially
- Document any special license requirements

## Docker
- Docker configurations should be included in repository
- Use Docker secrets or environment variables for sensitive data
- Never commit Docker images or large binary files
